This paper deals with analyzing query suggestion features of search engines, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the study focuses on person-related search suggestions, which could also fall under social media (cs.SOC) or computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it involves analyzing language patterns. The study also involves statistical analysis, which could fall under cybernetics (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
